A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Transportation – Identification Cards – Issuance to Minors
3 FOR the purpose of prohibiting the Motor Vehicle Administration from requiring a parent
4 or legal guardian of a minor at least a certain age to cosign or be present at the time
5 of submission of the minor’s application for an identification card; and generally
6 relating to State–issued identification cards for minors.
7 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
8 Article – Transportation
9 Section 12–301(a)
10 Annotated Code of Maryland
11 (2020 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
12 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
13 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
14 Article – Transportation
15 12–301.
16 (a) (1) On application, the Administration shall issue an identification card to
17 any applicant who:
18 [(1)] (I) Is a resident of this State;
19 [(2)] (II) Does not have a driver’s license;
20 [(3)] (III) Presents a birth certificate or other proof of age and identity
21 acceptable to the Administration;
